        <abstract>
            <p>Compares Jamaican with British and European honey combs.</p>
            <p>Requests one-half dozen dead bees and 2 or 3 drones from Mr Wilkie’s stock.</p>
            <p>His admiration for RH’s varied accomplishments and service "in the sacred cause of humanity" [the abolition of slavery].</p>
            <p>Asks whether it is believed that domestic animals long bred in Jamaica tend to assume a particular colour or character.</p>
            <p>Are differences observed in the West Indies in the liability of pure Europeans of light complexion and hair to take the yellow fever or other tropical complaints?</p>
        </abstract>
